lz, Germany":"Framersheim, Landkreis Alzey-Worms, Rheinland-Pfalz, Duitsland","Framersheim, Alzey, Hesse, Germany":"Framersheim, Alzey, Hessen, Duitsland","Framersheim, Rhineland-Pfalz, Palatinate, Germany":"Pfalz, Bayern, Duitsland"},"en":{"about 1620–after 1670":"about 1620–after 1670","1625–1650":"1625–1650","1645–1690":"1645–1690","1650–Female":"1650–Deceased","1650–1693":"1650–1693","1645–Female":"1645–Deceased","1620–1670":"1620–1670","from 1645 to 1660":"from 1645 to 1660","before 1650":"before 1650","1693":"1693","1670":"1670","1690":"1690","1645":"1645","1620":"1620","about 1645":"about 1645","1650":"1650","about 1620":"about 1620","after 1670":"after 1670","after 1650":"after 1650","about 1650":"about 1650","1625":"1625","Framersherim, Rheinland Pfalz, Germany":"Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany","Rhineland Germany":"Rhineland, Prussia","Framersheim, Alzey-Worms, Rheinland-Pfalz, Germany":"Framersheim, Alzey-Worms, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany","Framersheim, Alzey, Hesse, Germany":"Framersheim, Alzey, Hesse, Germany","Framersheim, Rhineland-Pfalz, Palatinate, Germany":"Palatinate, Bavaria, Germany","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wendel","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Hans, Helmut, Otto, Aloys, Bodo, Egon, Elke, Erwin, Frieda, Gerhard, Jurgen, Katharina.","German, Swedish, Danish, and Dutch: from the German personal name <i>Wendel</i>, a pet form of a short form, <i>Wando</i>, of a compound ancient Germanic name beginning with <i>wand</i> ‘to go, to migrate’.","German: metonymic occupational name for a turner, from Middle High German <i>wendel</i> ‘to turn’ or Middle Low German <i>wendelen</i> ‘to turn, twist’."],"variants":[{"name":"Wendelin","meanings":["South German: from the personal name <i>Wendelin</i>, a pet form of   Wendel  . <i>Wendelin</i> is the name of a Christian saint venerated in the Saarland, Germany.","Swedish: habitational name from a place called Vendel + the adjectival suffix <i>-in</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>-in(i)us</i> ‘relating to’. In some cases it may also be of German origin (see 1 above)."]},{"name":"Wendl","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Hans.","South German (Bavaria and Austria): variant of   Wendel  ."]},{"name":"Wendler","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Arno, Kurt, Siegbert, Claus, Erwin, Ewald, Gerd, Hans, Helmut, Helmuth, Otto.","German:","from Middle High German <i>wandeler</i> ‘traveler on foot’ (Middle Low German <i>wendeler</i>), hence a nickname for a pilgrim or an occupational name for a peddler."]},{"name":"Wandell","meanings":["Variant of   Wendel  ."]},{"name":"Wendell","meanings":["German, Swedish, and Danish: variant of   Wendel   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this (which can be also of Dutch origin). The surname <i>Wendell</i> is (very) rare in Germany, Sweden, and Denmark.","History: A prominent New Netherland (now NY) merchant family of this name descended from a colonist from Emden, Germany, which was part of the Netherlands in the 17th century."]},{"name":"Wendle","meanings":["South German: variant of   Wendel   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this."]},{"name":"Wandel","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Hans, Gerhard, Horst, Klaus.","German and Dutch: variant of   Wendel  .","Flemish (<b>De Wandel</b>): nickname for a pilgrim or an occupational name for a peddler, or a nickname for an unreliable person."]},{"name":"Windels","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Gerhard, Lothar.","German: patronymic from (a variant of) the personal name   Wendel  .","North German: metronymic from a short form of the female personal names <i>Windelheid</i> or <i>Windelmod</i>."]},{"name":"Wendling","meanings":["German:","habitational name from any of numerous places called Wendling, notably in Bavaria, or a place called Wendlingen, for example near Stuttgart.","(Westphalia): patronymic from the personal name <i>Wendel</i> (see   Wendel   1)."]}]},{"name":"Philipp","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Greek.  See  <b>Philip</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Philip","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Philipp Wendel was born about 1620, in Framersheim, Alzey, Hesse, Germany. He married Anna in 1645, in Framersheim, Alzey-Worms, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. He died after 1670, in Framersheim, Alzey-Worms, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany."},"et":{"about 1620–after 1670":"umbes 1620–pärast 1670","1625–1650":"1625–1650","1645–1690":"1645–1690","1650–Female":"1650–Surnud","1650–1693":"1650–1693","1645–Female":"1645–Surnud","1620–1670":"1620–1670","from 1645 to 1660":"1645 kuni 1660","before 1650":"enne 1650","1693":"1693","1670":"1670","1690":"1690","1645":"1645","1620":"1620","about 1645":"umbes 1645","1650":"1650","about 1620":"umbes 1620","after 1670":"pärast 1670","after 1650":"pärast 1650","about 1650":"umbes 1650","1625":"1625","Framersherim, Rheinland Pfalz, Germany":"Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Rhineland Germany":"Rheinprovinz, Preußen","Framersheim, Alzey-Worms, Rheinland-Pfalz, Germany":"Framersheim, Landkreis Alzey-Worms, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Framersheim, Alzey, Hesse, Germany":"Framersheim, Alzey, Hessen, Saksamaa","Framersheim, Rhineland-Pfalz, Palatinate, Germany":"Pfalz, Bayern, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"about 1620–after 1670":"noin 1620–1670 jälkeen","1625–1650":"1625–1650","1645–1690":"1645–1690","